      • isDefaultForm

        public boolean isDefaultForm​()
        Checks whether this form is a default form.

        A form is considered a default form if no form name is specified. Specifically, the system determines whether a form is a default form based on the value of the isDefault attribute defined under forms in the config.json file of the HarmonyOS application.

        Returns:
        Returns true if this form is a default form; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        4

        Returns:
        Returns the default grid style. The supported grid styles are 1 (one row and two columns), 2 (two rows and two columns), 3 (2 rows and 4 columns), and 4 (4 rows and 4 columns).
